        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 17
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 33
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "\"Who will go and work for me today?",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 17
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 31
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Who will bring to Me the lost and dying?",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 18
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 34
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Who will point them to the narrow way?\"",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 20
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 34
      } ]
    } ]
  }, {
    "type" : "chorus",
    "label" : "Chorus",
    "lines" : [ {
      "text" : "Speak, my Lord, speak, my Lord,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 16
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 26
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Speak, and I'll be quick to answer Thee;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 19
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 35
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Speak, my Lord, speak, my Lord,"
    }, {
      "text" : "Speak, and I will answer, \"Lord, send me.\"",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 18
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 38
      } ]
    } ]
  }, {
    "type" : "verse",
    "label" : "Verse 2",
    "lines" : [ {
      "text" : "When the coal of fire touched the prophet,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 17
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 34
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Making him as pure as pure can be,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 14
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 31
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "When the voice of God, said \"Who'll go for us?\"",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 18
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 43
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Then he answered, \"Here I am Lord send me.\"",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 18
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 39
      } ]
    } ]
  }, {
    "type" : "verse",
    "label" : "Verse 3",
    "lines" : [ {
      "text" : "Millions now in sin and shame are dying;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 16
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 34
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Listen to their sad and bitter cry;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 16
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 31
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Hasten, brother hasten to the rescue;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 16
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 30
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Quickly answer, \"Master, here am I.\"",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 16
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 33
      } ]
    } ]
  }, {
    "type" : "verse",
    "label" : "Verse 4",
    "lines" : [ {
